<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property">
  A <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> specifies text based
properties of a  
  <express_ref
    linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>
or
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>.   
  <example number="1">
    The character code, such as 'EBCDIC', used in the document.
  </example>
  
  <p>
    When the <b>Descriptive_document_property </b> is applied to a 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Digital_document_definition"/>
    through the <b>described_element</b> attribute, the
    <b>Descriptive_document_property </b> applies to all 
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Digital_file"/>s
    that are components of the 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Digital_document_definition"/>.
  </p>

  <p>
    When the <b>Descriptive_document_property </b> is applied to a 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Physical_document_definition"/>
    through the <b>described_element</b> attribute, the
    <b>Descriptive_document_property </b> applies to all 
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.Hardcopy"/>s
    that are components of the 
    <express_ref 
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Physical_document_definition"/>.
  </p>

  <p>
    When the <b>Descriptive_document_property </b> is applied to a 
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>  
    through the <b>described_element</b> attribute, the
    <b>Descriptive_document_property </b> applies to the individual 
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>.
  </p>

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  Attribute: property_type 
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
  linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_type">  A set of <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>s that identify similar 
characteristics are grouped into a category.
The property_type attribute identifies the category to which the
  property belongs.

  <p>
    Where applicable, the following categories shall be used:    
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
    'document content': a category of properties that
    detail the content of a given 
    <express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
    <example number="1">
      Examples of <b>Descriptive_document_properties</b> categorized as 
    'document content' properties are:
  <ul>
    <li>
      'detail_level': the level of detail that the 
      <express_ref 
        linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>
      provides. An example value for the 'detail_level' property is
      'rough 3d shape' - a 3D shape model without edge rounds and fillets. 
        <note>
          The name of the property 'detail_level' is stored in the
          <b>property_name</b> attribute of the
          <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> and the value of the
          property 'rough 3d shape' is stored in the
          <b>property_value</b> attribute of the
          <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>. 
        </note>
    </li>      

    <li>
      'geometry_type': the kind or kinds of geometry that the
      <express_ref 
        linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>
      contains. An example value for the 'geometry_type' property is
      '3D wireframe model' - The document contains a 3D shape model in
      wireframe representation;  
    </li>
   
    <li>
      'languages':
        the language or languages that are used in the
      <express_ref 
        linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>. 
      An example value for the 'languages' property are: 'Japanese' and
      'German' indicating annotation on a drawing is provided in the
      language 'Japanese' or 'German' respectively. 
    </li>
  </ul>
</example>
    </li>

    <li>
      'document creation': a category of properties that detail
      the context of creation of a <express_ref
linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>. 
    <example number="2">
      Examples of <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> 
      categorized as 'document creation' properties are:
    <ul>
      <li>
        'creating_system': 
        The creating_system specifies the computer application or the machine
        which is used to create the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
      </li>
      <li>
        'creating_interface':
        The creating_interface specifies the computer application used to
        create the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.       
An example value for the 'creating_interface' property is:
          'Postscript Printer Driver' indicating that a Postscript Printer
Driver was used to create a Physical_document.
      </li>
      <li>
        'operating_system':
        The operating_system specifies the operating system that is used to
        execute the computer application that created the
        
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>. 
      </li>
    </ul>
  </example>
  </li>
  <li>
    'document format': a category of properties that describe
    the format of a 
    <express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.

    <example number="3">
      Examples of <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> 
      categorized as 'document format' properties are:
    <ul>
      <li>
        'data_format':
        The data_format specifies the convention that was used to structure
        the information in the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
        'ISO 10303-21' is an example of a data format indicating that the
        document contains data in ISO 10303-21 format.
      </li>

      <li>
        'character_code':
        The character_code specifies the character code that is used in the
        
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
          'binary' is an example of a character code
          indicating that the document contains data in binary format;         
      </li>

   <li>
     'size_format':
     The size_format specifies the dimensions of a physical presentation of
     the 
<express_ref
      linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
       'ISO A0' is an example for the size_format of a drawing that is
       stored digitally.
   </li>

    </ul>
  </example>
  </li>
</ul>

</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Document_properties_arm  Entity: Descriptive_document_property  Attribute: property_name 
   <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
linkend="Document_properties_arm.Descriptive_document_property.property_name">
  The property_name specifies the name of the
  <b>Descriptive_document_property</b> that is assigned to the
  <express_ref
    linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
  <example number="4">
    'geometry_type' is a name given to the <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>
    that specifies the kind or kinds of geometry that an object
    contains. An example value for the 'geometry_type' property is
    '3D wireframe model' - The document contains a 3D shape model in
      wireframe representation;  
  </example>
  <example number="5">
    'size_format' is a name given to the <b>Descriptive_document_property</b>
     that specifies the dimensions of a physical presentation of
     the 
<express_ref
  linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.
'ISO A0', 'ISO A4' are example values for the size_format of a drawing that
is stored digitally.
  </example>
</ext_description>
